></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/41/1387341.jpg?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Used to be</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">i used to use this method on the harvest spell (10 sec casting) all the time, until it was nerfed.  Could cast harvest , hotkey a /sit on command, wait until its about to stun you, and hotkey a /sit off command.  Now this method wont work using casted spells from your spellbook.  I was told however, that items with a casting time on them can still be taken advantage of in this manner, and would work in the same exact way.   <br>
<br>
If the robe doesnt show a casting bar, counting in your head or stop watch would give you the same exact results...  <br>
<br>
Interesting  and worth using if the robe has a big casting time, lots of potential mana to be regened during that downtime :)<br>
<br>
