RZ</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udominifitusdarcana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dominifitus Darcana</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>9:42:33 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://darkband.freeservers.com/images/eq000002.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: I figured it out</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Believe it or not, I actually use this technigue with my solist's icy wand.<br>
<br>
When solo, and I have a mob reduced to the point it attempts to flee, I finish them off with my icy wand. I went into options and made the &quot;s&quot; key execute sit/stand. I right click the wand and hit &quot;s&quot;, med for several seconds, hit &quot;s&quot; and repeat. My icy wand never stops glowing hehe.<br>
<br>
Since the icy wand only does a max 38 pts of dmg I have regained a substantial amount of mana by the time the mob is killed, also saving the mana it would normally cost to finish the mob with another costly nuke. I would normally be on my back side medding regardless, so I have found that this method somewhat helps to reduce my downtime. So far, in my experiences, the fleeing mob has never ran out of range...works great and beats the hell out of playing gems.</font><P>[53 Channeler] Dominifitus (Erudite)<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucenelrontanknpuller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cenelron TankNPuller</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>4/3/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>7:10:55 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: I figured it out</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Here is how to do a macro for using the robe and medding.  Put your macro and your robe activation buttons together.  I have my macro button as number 3 and my robe button as number 4 in my example.  Set your macro up as follows:<br>
<br>
/sit off<br>
/pause 6<br>
/sit on<br>
/pause 200<br>
/sit off<br>
<br>
<br>
Type the 3,4 in rapid succession.  When you type the three that will immediately make you stand up (if sitting) and give you approximately one second to type the 4 (that's why you just type them quickly).  you will then sit down for about 23 seconds and automatically stand up at that point before the robe goes off.  When low on mana I go entire fights just typing 3,4 and using no mana.  Against most 45+ mobs you can still get in three or more robe blasts and contribute damage.  <br>
<br>
Be warned that the pause times seem to vary based upon the zone.  I have had to reduce the second pause to as low as 140 in Wakening Lands and increase it to as high as 205 in some other zone (I forget which).  The pause command seems to vary based on lag or something like that.<br>
<br>
Personally I think it is absolutely ridiculous that Shaman are given a bracer which drops (don't know where) that does 260 damage every 8 seconds and we, the masters of direct damage, are given a 360 damage robe that is EXTREMELY difficult to obtain that takes 28 seconds to use.  Verant HIGHLY over estimates the value of Lure spells.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR></TABLE><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=95%><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm7.showMessage?topicID=37.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm7.showMessage?topicID=43.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95% BORDER=0><TR><TD><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=9><IMG SRC=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm7.emailToFriend?topicID=21.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/images/email.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Email This To a Friend"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;Email This To a Friend</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm7.threadControl?topicID=21.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Topic Control Image"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;Topic Commands (Moderator only)</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm7.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=21.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Subscribe</FONT></A>  <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Click to receive email notification of replies</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm7.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=21.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Unsubscribe</FONT></A>  <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SI